getInstanceNumber

public String getInstanceNumber()
A number that identifies this composite object instance.

Please not that this is an IS DICOM value, which is supposed to be encoded in JAVA as an int. Nevertheless, String has been chosen because:

  • I have already seen objects, which uses non-numeric values for this identifiers.
  • For identifiers, the non-numeric value may still of some use/information as opposed to e.g. a non-numeric Frame Number..

Type 3
